  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice the <strong>brown&nbsp;onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Place an ice pack (Gousto's are perfect) or loose ice cubes into a bowl of <strong>cold water</strong> and set aside &ndash; this is your <strong>ice bath</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-spiced-veggie-kedgeree/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>eggs</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled salted water</strong> (the salt prevents them from cracking) bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook for 7 min for perfect mid-boiled eggs</p>\r\n<p>Once boiled, transfer&nbsp;the <strong>eggs</strong> to the <strong>ice bath</strong> and set aside</p>\r\n<p>Re-boil the kettle&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-spiced-veggie-kedgeree/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to&nbsp;<strong>tin foil</strong> and place on a baking tray, folding the edges around the tomatoes to collect any juices</p>\r\n<p>Drizzle them with <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>cashew nuts</strong> to the other end and put the tray in the oven for 7 min or until the cashews have coloured slightly</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-spiced-veggie-kedgeree/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>vegetable</strong>&nbsp;<strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;in 800ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.6L]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> saffron</strong> to the <strong>stock</strong> and stir well until it&rsquo;s a bright yellow colour</p>\r\n<p>Transfer the <strong>cashew nuts</strong> to a chopping board to cool</p>\r\n<p>Reduce the oven temperature to&nbsp;150&deg;C/ 130&deg;C (fan)/ 300&deg;F/ Gas 2 and return the <strong>tomatoes</strong> to the oven until serving, approx. 20-25 min</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Lato; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-spiced-veggie-kedgeree/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> <br /><br />Cook&nbsp;for 5 min, then add the <strong>curry powder</strong> and cook for a further 2 min until the onion has softened<br /><br />Add the <strong>arborio&nbsp;rice</strong> and <strong>sultanas</strong> and stir until both are evenly coated in oil and spice</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-spiced-veggie-kedgeree/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>stock</strong> to the rice, a ladle at a time, stirring frequently for 15-20 min or until all the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Tip: the more you stir, the creamier the rice will become!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-spiced-veggie-kedgeree/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>cashew nuts</strong> coarsely</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>cooled eggs</strong> and slice them in half</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-spiced-veggie-kedgeree/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the cooked creamy <strong>rice</strong> in bowls with the <strong>eggs</strong>, <strong>tomatoes</strong>, <strong>nuts</strong> and <strong>coriander</strong> to garnish</p>\r\n<p>Serve the <strong>lemon wedges</strong> to the side</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
